    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i feel like you're saying debt reduction is basically the only way to be \"responsible.\" if a country is struggling with poverty or bad schools, isn't it kind of shortsighted to worry about a debt number when people are suffering right now? shouldn't the human cost be more important than the fiscal math?",
